<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Write Now — Privacy Policy</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f5f5f7;
      --card: rgba(255,255,255,0.82);
      --text: #1d1d1f;
      --secondary: #6e6e73;
      --line: rgba(60,60,67,0.16);
      --accent: #0071e3;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "SF Pro Text", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(0,113,227,0.10), transparent 32%),
        var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .wrap {
      max-width: 920px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 48px 20px 80px;
    }

    .hero {
      margin-bottom: 28px;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 52px);
      line-height: 1.05;
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .intro {
      font-size: 19px;
      color: var(--secondary);
      max-width: 760px;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .meta {
      margin-top: 18px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--secondary);
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--card);
      backdrop-filter: saturate(180%) blur(24px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: saturate(180%) blur(24px);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 24px;
      padding: 28px;
      box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    }

    section + section {
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      line-height: 1.15;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin: 0 0 10px;
    }

    p {
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 10px 0 0 20px;
      padding: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    strong {
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .footer {
      margin-top: 22px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--secondary);
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .wrap { padding-top: 32px; }
      .card { padding: 22px; border-radius: 20px; }
      .intro { font-size: 17px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="wrap">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="eyebrow">Write Now</div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Write Now is built to minimize data collection. The app does not collect, store,
        sell, or share your personal data with the developer.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">
        Effective date: 06-03-2026<br />
        Developer: [INSERT YOUR NAME OR COMPANY NAME]<br />
        Contact: <a href="mailto:[INSERT CONTACT EMAIL]">[INSERT CONTACT EMAIL]</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="card">
      <section>
        <h2>1. Overview</h2>
        <p>
          Write Now is a speech-to-text utility designed with privacy in mind.
          The developer does not collect or maintain user profiles, and does not operate
          servers for storing your recordings or dictated text.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          The developer of Write Now does not collect personal data from users through the app.
        </p>
        <p>In particular, Write Now does not collect or store on the developer’s servers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>audio recordings;</li>
          <li>transcribed text;</li>
          <li>dictation history;</li>
          <li>account details;</li>
          <li>analytics linked to your identity;</li>
          <li>advertising or tracking identifiers.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Audio and Speech Processing</h2>
        <p>
          Write Now may use different speech recognition methods depending on the feature in use.
        </p>
        <p>
          When local speech models are used, audio processing is performed on the device by the app,
          and the developer does not transmit your recordings or transcribed content to external servers.
        </p>
        <p>
          Write Now may also use Apple-provided speech technologies. When Apple speech services are used,
          processing may occur on device or through Apple systems, depending on system configuration,
          device support, and service availability. Any such processing is subject to Apple’s own terms,
          settings, and privacy policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Text Content</h2>
        <p>
          The developer does not access, review, or store the text you dictate through Write Now,
          except for any temporary local processing required for the app to function on your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Local Device Storage</h2>
        <p>
          To provide core functionality, Write Now may store certain data locally on your device,
          such as app preferences, shortcuts, custom dictionary entries, or similar settings you create.
        </p>
        <p>
          This local data is not transmitted to the developer’s servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Permissions</h2>
        <p>
          Write Now may request access to the microphone and accessibility features solely to provide
          core app functionality, including capturing speech and inserting transcribed text into other apps.
        </p>
        <p>
          These permissions are not used for advertising, profiling, or unrelated tracking.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. No Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          Write Now does not track you across apps, websites, or services owned by other companies,
          and does not use third-party advertising SDKs for behavioral advertising.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Third-Party Platforms and Services</h2>
        <p>
          Some features may rely on Apple frameworks or system services. Those services are governed
          by Apple’s applicable terms and privacy policies. The developer is not responsible for the
          privacy practices of Apple or other platform providers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Write Now is not directed to children under the age required by applicable law to provide
          consent on their own, and the developer does not knowingly collect personal information from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any updates will be posted on this page
          with a revised effective date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact:
          <a href="mailto:[INSERT CONTACT EMAIL]">[INSERT CONTACT EMAIL]</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      © [INSERT YEAR] [INSERT YOUR NAME OR COMPANY NAME]. All rights reserved.
    </div>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
